    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Secular Songs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Crozet Duplantier letter disputes Jerry Leiber and Mike Stoller's September 9 letter on Ken Emerson's August 26 article on Brill Building; holds White Christmas and other songs reflect non-Christian sensibility</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>In a Sept. 9 letter regarding Ken Emerson's article on the Brill Building, Jerry Leiber and Mike Stoller dismiss the possibility of a ''Jewish sensibility'' in the building's songwriters, saying it's like ''implying that Irving Berlin's Jewishness influenced his writing of 'White Christmas.' '' But of course it did; or, at the very least, this song reflects a ''non-Christian'' sensibility. ''White Christmas'' (like ''Easter Parade'') belongs to that genre of song that celebrates the secular traditions of Christian holidays.</p>
        <p>CROZET DUPLANTIER  Chicago</p>
      </block>
